---
import { defaultLang, useTranslations } from "../i18n/utils";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const lang = defaultLang;
const t = useTranslations(lang);
const lastUpdated = "May 30, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - ReadAny"
  description="ReadAny privacy policy, including local-first storage, WebDAV sync, third-party AI providers, text-to-speech, diagnostics, and user rights."
>
  <Header lang={lang} t={t} />

  <main class="legal-main">
    <section class="legal-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">ReadAny</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        ReadAny is designed as a local-first reader. Your books, notes, highlights, bookmarks, reading progress,
        and settings stay on your device by default.
      </p>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </section>

    <article class="legal-content">
      <section>
        <h2>1. Information We Process</h2>
        <p>
          ReadAny may process the books you import, reading progress, highlights, annotations, bookmarks, notes,
          app settings, reading statistics, and optional AI or sync configuration you choose to set up.
        </p>
        <p>
          These items are primarily stored locally on your device. We do not operate a default cloud library that
          automatically uploads your reading content to ReadAny servers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Local Storage</h2>
        <p>
          Imported books and reading data are stored on your device so the app can provide offline reading,
          annotation, search, statistics, and playback features. Deleting the app or clearing local app data may
          remove this locally stored content, depending on your platform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Sync Services You Configure</h2>
        <p>
          If you enable WebDAV, S3, LAN sync, or another supported sync option, ReadAny sends the selected library
          data to the service and account you configure. We do not control those third-party or self-hosted services.
          Their privacy practices are governed by their own policies and your own server settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. AI, Translation, Embeddings, and TTS Providers</h2>
        <p>
          ReadAny lets you configure external AI, translation, embedding, and text-to-speech providers. When you use
          those features, selected text, prompts, book context, generated content, or audio requests may be sent to
          the provider you choose, such as an OpenAI-compatible endpoint, Gemini, Claude, Ollama, DeepSeek, Edge TTS,
          or another configured service.
        </p>
        <p>
          You are responsible for reviewing the privacy policy and data handling terms of each provider you connect.
          You can avoid sending content to external providers by not enabling those integrations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Diagnostics and Support</h2>
        <p>
          ReadAny does not require you to create an account for local reading. If you contact us through GitHub
          Issues, email, community channels, or other support paths, we may receive the information you decide to
          share, such as logs, screenshots, device information, or a description of the problem. Please avoid sending
          private book content unless it is necessary for support.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Purchases and App Stores</h2>
        <p>
          If you install or purchase ReadAny through an app store, purchase records, refunds, taxes, billing, and
          account details are handled by the relevant platform, such as Apple App Store or Google Play. We receive
          only the information those platforms make available to developers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          ReadAny is a general productivity and reading tool. We do not knowingly collect personal information from
          children. If you believe a child has provided personal information to us through a support channel, please
          contact us so we can handle the request appropriately.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Your Choices</h2>
        <p>
          You can manage your data by deleting books, notes, highlights, sync settings, AI provider settings, or local
          app data from within the app or through your operating system. You can also disable third-party integrations
          at any time by removing their configuration.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy as ReadAny evolves, including when new cloud, sync, AI, or subscription services
          become available. The latest version will be posted on this page with an updated date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions, open an issue at
          <a href="https://github.com/codedogQBY/ReadAny/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            github.com/codedogQBY/ReadAny/issues
          </a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer t={t} />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-main {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding-top: 3.5rem;
    background: var(--background);
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .legal-hero {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--card);
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3.5rem;
  }

  .legal-hero,
  .legal-content {
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1 {
    color: var(--foreground);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 750;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1.02;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .lede {
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 1.4rem 0 0;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .updated {
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal-content {
    padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem 5rem;
  }

  .legal-content section + section {
    margin-top: 2.4rem;
  }

  h2 {
    color: var(--foreground);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  p + p {
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.18em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal-hero {
      padding-top: 4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
